@@yCrumbling Obelisk@@N~
@@yA weathered stone obelisk rises from the sand, its carved hieroglyphs nearly obliterated by centuries of wind erosion. The base is surrounded by scattered rubble and half-buried stone blocks. Whatever monument once stood here has been reduced to this single defiant pillar.
  Fragments of colored tile and shattered pottery litter the ground around the obelisk's base, remnants of offerings left by long-dead pilgrims. The remaining hieroglyphs hint at warnings to trespassers, though the language is too ancient to decipher with certainty.@@N
