#29903
@@ySun-Baked Flats@@N~
@@yThe dunes give way to a broad hardpan flat baked to cracked ceramic by the relentless sun. Thin salt deposits create white veins across the tan earth. Bleached bones of unlucky travelers and animals litter the ground in scattered clusters.
  The flat extends in a broad sweep, its surface crackling underfoot like broken pottery. Dried salt flats shimmer blindingly where the sun catches them. The skeletal remains of a caravan wagon lie half-swallowed by the earth, its wooden ribs bleached to the same bone-white as the surrounding remains.@@N
