#29904
@@yBleached Bone Field@@N~
@@yCountless bones protrude from the cracked earth in grotesque arrangements, a graveyard of creatures that perished crossing this merciless flat. Vultures circle overhead, patient and watchful. The bones clatter softly whenever the wind picks up.
  Some of the larger skeletons are still partially articulated, frozen in their final moments of desperate crawling toward water that never came. Sun-cracked skulls grin upward at the pitiless sky. The ground between the remains is littered with rusted buckles, corroded coins, and fragments of sun-rotted leather.@@N
