@@yVulture's Perch@@N~
@@yA cluster of dead trees stands here, their bleached trunks stripped bare by the elements. Large vultures roost in the twisted branches, hunched and silent, occasionally spreading tattered wings to catch the thermal updrafts that rise from the scorching sand.
  The ground beneath the trees is splattered with droppings and littered with regurgitated bone pellets. The vultures regard all movement below with patient, calculating interest, their bald heads swiveling in eerie unison. A pungent carrion stench hangs thick in the still air.@@N
