#29906
@@yDry Riverbed@@N~
@@yA wide channel of smooth stones and cracked mud marks a river that dried up long ago. The banks rise steeply on either side, creating a natural corridor through the landscape. Occasional patches of thorny scrub have taken root between the water-worn rocks.
  Smooth river stones of every color carpet the channel floor, polished by centuries of rushing water that has long since vanished. Deep cracks in the dried mud have curled upward at the edges like brittle parchment. The shade from the high banks offers some relief from the sun, but the trapped air is stifling and still.@@N
