@@yAncient Well@@N~
@@yA circular stone well stands in a shallow depression, its rim worn smooth by countless hands over many centuries. The bucket rope has long since rotted away, and peering into the dark shaft reveals nothing but dry emptiness far below.
  Carved symbols ring the well's exterior, prayers to forgotten water gods etched by desperate hands. A faint, dry updraft rises from the shaft, carrying the dusty scent of deep stone. Several small offerings of beads and carved figurines have been left on the rim by travelers hoping the water might return.@@N
