@@yCanyon Mouth@@N~
@@yThe dry riverbed narrows into a steep-walled canyon, the rock faces scored with horizontal striations from ancient flood waters. A dark cave opening yawns in the southern wall, exhaling cool air that smells faintly of chitin and something worse.
  The canyon walls tower overhead, their layered strata telling a geological story of ancient seas and vanished rivers. Loose scree crunches underfoot, and the echoes of each footstep bounce between the narrow walls. Dark stains around the cave mouth suggest something regularly drags prey inside.@@N
