@@ySandstone Arch@@N~
@@yA natural arch of layered sandstone spans the trail here, eroded into a graceful curve by millennia of wind. The stone is banded in shades of amber and rust, and the sheltered area beneath offers a brief respite from the punishing desert sun.
  Travelers have scratched names and dates into the softer stone beneath the arch, some dating back centuries. A cairn of flat stones marks the junction of several trails, and small lizards bask on the sun-warmed rock, darting into crevices at the slightest disturbance.@@N
