@@yDesert Crossroads@@N~
@@ySeveral faint trails converge at this barren junction marked by a sun-bleached wooden signpost. The sign's painted directions have long since faded, leaving only bare splintered wood. Boot prints and cart tracks in the hard-packed sand suggest regular traffic heading east.
  A pile of discarded water skins and broken sandals marks this as a rest stop for desert travelers, though the picked-over remains suggest bandits monitor the crossroads. Scuff marks and dried bloodstains in the sand hint at ambushes past.@@N
