@@yPalm Grove@@N~
@@yA cluster of date palms grows from the sandy soil, their fronds providing blessed shade from the brutal sun. Fallen dates litter the ground, attracting insects and small lizards. The grove extends southward along a shallow depression in the terrain.
  The palms sway gently in a breeze that barely reaches the ground level, their rustling fronds creating a soothing whisper. Beetle tracks wind between the trunks, and the sweet fermenting smell of overripe dates mingles with the earthy scent of rare moisture in the soil.@@N
