@@yMerchant's Ruin@@N~
@@yThe collapsed remains of a merchant's outpost lie scattered across the sand. Broken wagon wheels, shattered pottery, and torn fabric speak to a violent end. Scorch marks on the remaining timbers suggest raiders were responsible for the destruction.
  A partially collapsed stone foundation is all that remains of what was once a trading post. Shards of glazed pottery from distant lands crunch underfoot, and faded scraps of silk flutter from splintered beams. The sand has already begun reclaiming the ruins.@@N
