@@yTemple Forecourt@@N~
@@ySmooth flagstones emerge from beneath the encroaching sand, forming a broad courtyard before an ancient structure to the south. Toppled columns line what was once a grand processional avenue, and faded carvings of desert deities adorn every stone surface.
  The scale of the architecture speaks to a civilization of great power and ambition. Fallen column drums lie scattered like discarded building blocks, each taller than a person. Traces of red and blue paint cling to protected crevices in the stone, hinting at the vibrant colors that once adorned this approach.@@N
