@@ySphinx Gate@@N~
@@yTwo enormous sphinx statues flank a monumental gateway, their stone faces weathered but still radiating stern authority. The passage between them leads south into shadowed depths. To the east, a toppled colossus lies half-buried in the drifting sand.
  Each sphinx is carved from a single massive block of granite, their lion bodies crouched in eternal vigilance. Faint traces of gold leaf still cling to their headdresses, and their eyes seem to track movement with unsettling awareness. The gateway between them exhales cold, tomb-scented air.@@N
