@@yCracked Colossus@@N~
@@yA titanic stone statue lies broken on its side, half-consumed by the desert. The carved face still bears traces of painted features, gazing skyward with sightless eyes. Sand has drifted into the cracks and hollows of the enormous form.
  The colossus must have stood thirty feet tall when whole. Its outstretched stone hand lies palm-up in the sand, large enough to stand in. Chisel marks along the fracture line suggest the toppling was deliberate, perhaps by conquering invaders seeking to erase the memory of the king it depicted.@@N
