#29946
@@bNecromancer's Workshop@@N~
@@bThis cluttered chamber served as a workspace for dark rituals. Stone tables hold fragments of bone, dusty vials of dark liquid, and crumbling scrolls covered in forbidden incantations. Chalk circles and arcane diagrams cover the floor.
  The work tables are cluttered with the detritus of necromantic experimentation: bone fragments arranged in geometric patterns, crystallized reagents in cracked glass vials, and yellowed scrolls whose text writhes when viewed from the corner of one's eye. The chalk diagrams on the floor overlap in layers, each more complex than the last.@@N
