#29947
@@bLich's Antechamber@@N~
@@bThe temperature drops sharply in this frost-rimed corridor. Ice crystals coat the walls despite the desert above, and each breath comes as a visible cloud. The oppressive weight of powerful magic presses down from all sides, growing stronger to the south.
  Icicles hang from the ceiling in unnatural formations, some curving sideways as if grown under the influence of warped magical fields. The frost on the walls forms patterns that resemble screaming faces when viewed at certain angles. A deep thrumming vibration rises through the floor, rhythmic as a heartbeat.@@N
