#29949
@@bCollapsed Dead End@@N~
@@bThe tunnel here has partially collapsed, filling the passage with rubble and broken masonry. Fragments of carved stone and shattered pottery are mixed into the debris. A few skeletal hands protrude from beneath the fallen rock.
  The collapse appears ancient, the fallen stones now cemented together by mineral deposits and centuries of slow moisture seepage. The skeletal hands reaching from the rubble are frozen in desperate clawing gestures, their owners crushed during whatever catastrophe brought down the ceiling.@@N
