#29950
@@bCave Entrance@@N~
@@bThe canyon narrows into a dark cave mouth, the rock walls slick with moisture from some underground source. The temperature drops noticeably as the desert sun is left behind. Claw marks score the stone floor, and the acrid smell of venom permeates the air.
  The transition from blazing daylight to cave darkness is abrupt and disorienting. Water seeps down the walls in thin rivulets, feeding patches of pale moss that cling to the damp stone. Deep gouges in the cave floor, each several inches wide, suggest the passage of something with enormous claws or a heavy segmented body.@@N
