#29952
@@bChitinous Cavern@@N~
@@bThe walls of this natural cavern are encrusted with shed scorpion shells and dried husks of molted exoskeletons. The floor crunches with every step, carpeted in fragments of chitin. Larger intact shells hang from the ceiling like grotesque decorations.
  Some of the shed exoskeletons are remarkably intact, hollow replicas of the creatures that wore them, split along the back where their owners crawled free. The chitinous carpet crunches and pops with a stomach-turning sound, and a dry, musty odor fills the enclosed space.@@N
