#29953
@@bEgg Chamber@@N~
@@bClusters of translucent eggs the size of melons are attached to every surface of this warm, humid cavern. Some are dark and empty, while others pulse with the movement of developing larvae within. A thick resinous substance holds the clusters in place.
  The humid air is nearly suffocating, heavy with a sweet organic smell. The viable eggs glow with a faint amber luminescence, and the developing larvae within can be seen curling and uncurling in their gelatinous sacs. Freshly hatched nymphs, pale and nearly transparent, scatter into crevices at any disturbance.@@N
