#29954
@@bWebbed Passage@@N~
@@bThick strands of sticky webbing crisscross this passage, making progress difficult. Wrapped bundles hanging from the ceiling contain the desiccated remains of unfortunate creatures. The webs vibrate faintly with the movement of their creator somewhere nearby.
  The silk is incredibly strong, requiring considerable force to break through. Several of the hanging bundles are disturbingly humanoid in shape, and one still wears the tattered remains of a leather boot protruding from its cocoon. The web strands thrum like bowstrings at the slightest touch.@@N
