#29955
@@bGlowing Grotto@@N~
@@bBioluminescent fungi cling to the damp walls of this spacious grotto, casting everything in an eerie blue-green light. The soft glow reveals a cavern of surprising beauty, with mineral formations creating natural pillars and curtains of crystallized stone.
  The fungi grow in overlapping shelves of luminous blue and green, pulsing gently as if breathing. Stalactites and stalagmites have fused into flowing columns of crystalline calcite that sparkle in the bioluminescent glow. Tiny cave crickets hop between the fungal colonies, their translucent bodies glowing briefly as they feed.@@N
