#29956
@@bMolten Crack@@N~
@@bA fissure in the cave floor reveals a distant orange glow of magma far below. Waves of heat rise from the crack, and the surrounding stone is warm to the touch. Mineral deposits along the edges have crystallized into colorful formations.
  The fissure splits the cavern floor in a jagged line, its edges lined with crystals of sulfur and iron oxide in vivid yellows and reds. The heat radiating upward creates shimmering distortions in the air, and occasional deep rumbles from below send fine vibrations through the surrounding stone.@@N
