#29957
@@bScorpion Nest@@N~
@@bThis large cavern is littered with the remains of countless prey animals, bones picked clean and scattered across the sandy floor. Deep grooves in the stone show where massive scorpion tails have dragged across the surface repeatedly.
  The bone piles include creatures of every size, from small rodents to what appears to be a full-grown desert horse. The tail grooves are worn inches deep into solid rock, testament to the age and size of the creatures that nest here. A thick musky scent permeates the chamber, marking it as actively occupied territory.@@N
