#29958
@@bVenomous Lair@@N~
@@bPools of caustic venom have collected in natural depressions across the floor of this foul-smelling cave. The liquid gives off acrid fumes that sting the eyes and throat. Corroded bones and dissolved equipment mark where victims met their end.
  The venom pools are an oily yellow-green, their surfaces occasionally bubbling as chemical reactions continue breaking down submerged material. Metal equipment has been reduced to pitted, barely recognizable lumps. The fumes are so concentrated that eyes water and the back of the throat burns with each breath.@@N
