#29959
@@bBrood Chamber@@N~
@@bSmaller scorpions of various sizes scuttle across the walls and ceiling of this cramped cave. Hundreds of tiny eyes glint in the darkness, and the constant click of small pincers creates an unsettling chorus. This appears to be a nursery of sorts.
  The juvenile scorpions range from fingernail-sized nymphs to adolescents the size of a fist, all sharing the same aggressive territorial behavior as their enormous parents. They swarm over each other in competing clusters, occasionally erupting into brief cannibalistic skirmishes. The clicking and scraping of hundreds of tiny legs creates an unceasing white noise.@@N
