#29960
@@bQueen's Antechamber@@N~
@@bThe tunnel widens dramatically here, the walls polished smooth by the passage of something enormous. Deep gouges in the stone floor and a thick coating of dried venom on every surface mark this as the threshold of a powerful creature's domain.
  The polished walls reflect a distorted mirror of everything in the tunnel, smeared with a waxy residue from the creature's passage. The venom coating has calcified into a crystalline crust that crunches underfoot and releases a sharp chemical odor when broken. The scale of the gouges in the floor suggest a creature of truly terrifying proportions.@@N
