#29961
@@RScorpion Queen's Den@@N~
@@RA vast natural cathedral opens up, its ceiling lost in darkness far above. The floor is a carpet of crushed bones and discarded chitin, and massive scorpion tracks crisscross every surface. The air is thick with the chemical reek of concentrated venom.
  The cavern is immense, its walls curving up and away into unseen heights. Massive stalactites hang from the darkness above like stone fangs, and the bone-littered floor crunches with every step. The concentrated venom fumes are nearly overwhelming, and the echoes of distant clicking and scraping reverberate from every direction.@@N
