#29962
@@bHidden Burrow@@N~
@@bA narrow side passage leads to this small, secluded cavern partially hidden behind a curtain of mineral deposits. The floor is covered in fine sand, and claw marks suggest something uses this as a private resting place away from the larger cave system.
  The mineral curtain creates a natural doorway of translucent flowstone, partially concealing the burrow from the main tunnel. The sand floor shows compressed body impressions where a reptilian creature has coiled repeatedly. A small collection of gnawed bones and shed scales litters one corner.@@N
