#29963
@@yDesert Trail@@N~
@@yA worn trail cuts through the sand heading east, marked by occasional cairns of stacked stones. Boot prints and the ruts of heavily laden carts have packed the sand into a firm path. The tracks all lead toward a fortified encampment visible in the distance.
  Discarded refuse and broken equipment litter the trail margins, dropped by passing raiders too lazy to dispose of them properly. Crude warning totems fashioned from animal skulls and feathers mark the approach at intervals, growing more frequent as the camp draws nearer. The acrid smell of smoke and unwashed bodies carries on the wind.@@N
