#29965
@@yPalisade Gate@@N~
@@ySharpened wooden stakes lashed together with rope form a crude palisade wall. A gap serves as the main gate into the raider encampment beyond. Skulls mounted on poles flank the entrance as a grim warning to anyone foolish enough to approach uninvited.
  The palisade is reinforced with stolen wagon parts and scavenged timber, lashed together with a mix of rope and leather thongs. The skulls flanking the gate are sun-bleached and cracked, their jaws wired shut with copper wire. Scratch marks on the gate posts show where blades are regularly tested against the wood.@@N
