#29968
@@yWeapon Rack@@N~
@@yRows of crude wooden racks hold an assortment of weapons in various states of repair. Notched blades, dented maces, and splintered spear shafts are sorted roughly by type. A grinding wheel and anvil nearby show signs of recent use for maintenance.
  The weapons range from serviceable to barely functional, most showing the nicks and stains of heavy use. A whetstone sits in a bucket of murky water beside the grinding wheel, and metal filings dust the packed sand beneath the anvil. The air smells of iron filings and weapon oil.@@N
