#29969
@@yCampfire Ring@@N~
@@yA large fire pit ringed with flat stones serves as the social center of the raider camp. Charred logs and glowing embers fill the pit, and crude log benches surround it. The sand is littered with bone fragments and empty drink skins from nightly revelry.
  Scorch marks and spilled ash extend well beyond the stone ring, evidence of fires that grew larger than intended during drunken celebrations. Carved tally marks on the log benches keep score of fights and wagers. The embers still glow hot beneath a layer of white ash, ready to be stoked for the evening meal.@@N
