#29970
@@ySlave Pen@@N~
@@yA section of the camp has been fenced off with rope and stakes to form a crude holding pen. Iron shackles are bolted to heavy rocks, and the trampled sand is stained with old blood. The miserable conditions speak to the raiders' cruelty.
  The shackle chains are rusted but strong, attached to boulders too heavy for any bound captive to move. A crude water trough sits empty and crusted with dried algae. The stench of suffering and fear lingers in the trampled sand, and tattered scraps of clothing caught on the rope fence flutter in the hot wind.@@N
