#29971
@@yFighting Pit@@N~
@@yA circular depression has been dug into the sand and lined with flat stones to form a crude arena. Dark stains cover the pit floor, and spectator benches made from looted wagon boards ring the perimeter. This is where the raiders settle disputes.
  The pit floor is stained dark with old blood that no amount of sand can fully absorb. Notches carved into the stone rim keep a grim tally of fights and their outcomes. Discarded weapons too damaged to reuse are piled in a corner, and the spectator benches are worn smooth from regular use.@@N
