#29974
@@yTreasure Hoard@@N~
@@yChests and strongboxes taken from merchant caravans are piled in this guarded corner of the camp. Most have been broken open, their contents sorted and divided. Coins, gemstones, and trade goods spill from overflowing containers.
  The plunder represents dozens of successful raids, with goods from across the known trade routes piled in careless abundance. Bolts of fine cloth lie in the sand beside sacks of exotic spices and casks of aged wine. The broken locks and splintered lids tell stories of hasty, brutal access. Despite the wealth on display, guards watch it with the jealous vigilance of those who have killed to take it.@@N
